  "prompt": "I scored 72% in 10th and 88% in 12 can I be able to became ias officer?",
  "response": "Yes, you can become an IAS (Indian Administrative Service) officer if you have scored 72% in 10th and 88% in 12th. The eligibility criteria for appearing in the IAS exam (part of the Civil Services Examination conducted by the UPSC) primarily focus on educational qualifications, and not directly on your school percentages.\n\nTo become an IAS officer, you need to complete a bachelor's degree from a recognized university. After obtaining your degree, you can prepare for the UPSC Civil Services Examination, which consists of three stages: the Preliminary exam, the Mains exam, and the Interview (Personality Test).\n\nIn addition to educational qualifications, ensure that you prepare thoroughly for the exam, as it is highly competitive. Good luck with your aspirations to become an IAS officer!",
